-- Continental sees $3 billion cash, investments end quarter
-- 
-- Mon Sep 10, 2007 4:45pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/10/us-continental-idUSWEN088320070910

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Continental Airlines Inc CAL.N on Monday projected it would end its third quarter with about $3.0 billion in cash and short-term investments. 

 The airline also said it expected to grow mainline capacity, a measure of seats on its main routes, by 3 percent to 4 percent in 2008. (Reporting by  Peter Henderson )